{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"45fddeca-ef67-4ca5-8f18-0f5d75bfbf76","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nKey difference: xUnit embeds the skip reason directly in `[Fact]`/`[Theory]`, while the others use a separate attribute.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e42cc7da-a1df-4603-adea-0de53466ed5c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":309,"requestId":"A03C:243205:1822A1C:1B613C6:69FE8A4F"},"id":"4f7bb0ad-a730-45fd-9413-d9342cf0c1ab","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:13:57.100Z","parentId":"ad6b64f4-cea8-4ecc-a0f7-193191350434"}
